headline: COST- Richly Valued, But on the Right Track
summary: In a market high on AI hype and $10 billion chip orders, one of the best-performing stocks sells toilet paper in bulk. If you’re judging by long-term ownership, investor trust, and consistent outperformance with zero drama, you might want to look at Costco Wholesale Corp. (COST), advises Nicholas Vardy, editor of The Global Guru.

headline: How Surging Digital Sales in September at Costco (COST) Has Changed Its Investment Story
summary: Earlier in October 2025, Costco Wholesale reported net sales of US$26.58 billion for September, marking an 8% increase year over year and highlighting the company's continued momentum in both physical and digital sales channels. The introduction of "digitally-enabled" comparable sales, which rose over 26%, provides insight into Costco's success in leveraging e-commerce, strengthening its position as multichannel retail becomes increasingly important. With Costco's digital sales growth...
